@startuml loadbalancergui

' Styling for better readability
skinparam backgroundColor #2B2B2B
skinparam classBackgroundColor #333333
skinparam classBorderColor #FFFFFF
skinparam classFontColor #FFFFFF
skinparam classFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #FFFFFF
skinparam roundcorner 15
skinparam shadowing false

' LoadBalancerGUI JavaFX-based GUI
class LoadBalancerGUI {
    - static Logger logger
    - LoadBalancer balancer
    - TextArea statusArea

    + void start(Stage stage)
    + void addServerDialog()
    + void importLogs()
    + void balanceLoadDialog()
    + void generateReport()
    + void displayStatus()
    + void failServerDialog()
    + void log(String msg)
    + void alert(String title, String msg)
    + static void main(String[] args)
}

' LoadBalancerGUI depends on LoadBalancer for server management
LoadBalancerGUI --> "1" LoadBalancer : manages

' JavaFX components used in GUI
LoadBalancerGUI --> "1" Stage : main window
LoadBalancerGUI --> "1" TextArea : log output
LoadBalancerGUI --> "7" Button : interactive controls

' Logger integration
LoadBalancerGUI --> "1" Logger : logs events

' Explanation Note
note right of LoadBalancerGUI
    "Provides a JavaFX-based UI for LoadBalancerPro. 
    Includes logging, status updates, and interactive load balancing controls."
end note

title LoadBalancerGUI - JavaFX UI for Load Balancing

@enduml
